main event: A UFO observation reported in Riverside, New York on October 24, 1968, but no identifiable image could be found on the submitted polaroid prints.
interesting points: The investigation concluded that there was insufficient data to support a UFO sighting., The observer was asked to complete an AF Form 117, but has not done so as of May 21, 1969., The report included grainy, low-quality images that did not depict any clear objects., A letter from the Air Force expressed gratitude for the sighting report and mentioned further investigation., The witness described seeing two saucer-shaped objects that were maneuverable and disappeared quickly.
witness description: The report contains details from an unnamed witness.
